DataElement.preferredName: Prior First-Line Therapy Nab-paclitaxel Administered Ind
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A response used to determine whether or not a Cremophor EL-free, albumin-stabilized nanoparticle formulation of the natural taxane paclitaxel with antineoplastic activity was previously given as the preferred standard treatment for a particular condition.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: Earlier in time or order._The preferred standard treatment for a particular condition._A Cremophor EL-free, albumin-stabilized nanoparticle formulation of the natural taxane paclitaxel with antineoplastic activity. Paclitaxel binds to and stabilizes microtubules, preventing their depolymerization and so inhibiting cellular motility, mitosis, and replication. This formulation solubilizes paclitaxel without the use of the solvent Cremophor, thereby permitting the administration of larger doses of paclitaxel while avoiding the toxic effects associated with Cremophor._The act of having given something (e.g., a medication or test).

Concepts.definition: The preferred standard treatment for a particular condition.

A Cremophor EL-free, albumin-stabilized nanoparticle formulation of the natural taxane paclitaxel with antineoplastic activity. Paclitaxel binds to and stabilizes microtubules, preventing their depolymerization and so inhibiting cellular motility, mitosis, and replication. This formulation solubilizes paclitaxel without the use of the solvent Cremophor, thereby permitting the administration of larger doses of paclitaxel while avoiding the toxic effects associated with Cremophor.
The act of having given something (e.g., a medication or test).
